Planned cap on spending in old age
BBC Radio 4's Money Box
Saturday, 14th July 2012 at 1204 BST On Radio 4 and Online
Listen to the programme
Programme transcript (17 pages)
The Government said this week that it would set a cap on the total amount any individual had to pay for their care in old age.But a lot of key details were omitted, including what that cap should be or when it would begin. It did say that a new universal deferred payment scheme would begin from April 2015. But how new was that idea? We hear from Lisa Morgan, a partner at Hugh James solicitors. We also talk to Dot Gibson, General Secretary of the National Pensioners Forum and Gus Hanton, Co-Founder of the Intergenerational Foundation about who should pick up the cost of care. Related Links:
