Farepak payoutMore than 100,000 victims of the collapse of the Farepak Christmas club in 2006 will get a total of 50p for every pound they lost. And the money will be paid by this Christmas. They have already had 17.5p and another 32p is now due to be paid after LloydsTSB agreed to put £8 million into the fund following criticism form a judge in a court case. But how much are the administrators/liquidators getting? We speak to Louise McDaid who lost money in the Farepak collapse and Mike Dailly from the Govan Law Centre. Related Links:
