Flood insuranceThe Government is trying to persuade the insurance industry to make sure all homes can get flood insurance - even those at high risk. A deal between the insurance industry and the Government to make sure everyone can at least get insurance at some price runs out in June 2013. How will that affect the premiums we all pay in future? Mary Dhonau the Chief Executive of 'Know Your Flood Risk' campaign says it could get much harder for people to find insurance. Related Links:
